Z-axis: the reference axis passing through the origin, and extending toward the second surface R2;


Y-axis: a straight line passing through the origin, and forming 90 (degree)  in a counterclockwise direction with the Z-axis within the tilted surface (within the surface of FIG. 7); and


X-axis: a straight line passing through the origin, and perpendicular to the z-axis and y-axis (a straight line perpendicular to the surface of FIG. 7).
